---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services — Intelligence Layer Build, Diagnostic, and Advisory"
  description="Strategnik builds the Intelligence Layer — the foundational operating context that makes AI-native marketing possible. Diagnostic, sprint build, and ongoing advisory for Series B through pre-IPO B2B SaaS."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Services</p>
      <h1 class="text-display-lg mb-8 text-balance" data-animate-hero>
        Build the machine. Not the team.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body-lg text-gray-400" data-animate-hero-sub>
        I build the <a href="/intelligence-layer" class="text-blue-bright hover:text-white transition-colors">Intelligence Layer</a> — the foundational operating context that allows AI agents to run your marketing with the precision, style, and strategic intent of your best marketer. Not a chatbot. Not a consultant. The infrastructure that makes AI-native marketing actually work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who This Is For -->
  <section class="section-sm border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-heading mb-6" data-animate>Is this you?</h2>
      <div class="prose-minimal">
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
          You're a CEO, founder, or CRO at a Series B through pre-IPO B2B SaaS company. Your team has AI tools but nothing feels different. Output went up, pipeline didn't move. You're asking: Should I hire a Head of Marketing or build an AI-native system? How many marketers do I actually need? What does marketing look like in 18 months?
        </p>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.15">
          You can picture the problem. You cannot picture the solution. The Intelligence Layer makes the solution visible.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Engagement Ladder -->
  <section class="section border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="section-label">How I Work</p>
      <h2 class="text-display mb-12" data-animate>The Engagement Ladder</h2>

      <div class="space-y-16" data-animate-stagger="0.15">
        <!-- Diagnostic -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-small text-teal-400 mb-2">Entry Point</p>
          <h3 class="text-heading mb-4">Intelligence Layer Diagnostic</h3>
          <p class="text-body text-gray-400 mb-6">
            A 2-4 week assessment that maps your marketing function across all six components of the Intelligence Layer. Walk away with a gap analysis, an architecture blueprint, and a sequenced build plan — whether you engage further or hand it to your internal team.
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-small text-gray-400">
            <li>→ Six-component gap analysis (what exists, what's missing, what's broken)</li>
            <li>→ AI discoverability scorecard across ChatGPT, Perplexity, AI Overviews</li>
            <li>→ Execution tax quantification (hours, cost per output, signal-to-response latency)</li>
            <li>→ Architecture blueprint specific to your company, market, and stage</li>
            <li>→ Sequenced build plan with clear priorities</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sprint Build -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-small text-teal-400 mb-2">The Build</p>
          <h3 class="text-heading mb-4">Intelligence Layer Sprint</h3>
          <p class="text-body text-gray-400 mb-6">
            A 30-90 day engagement that builds and deploys the full Intelligence Layer — all six components encoded, documented, and connected to your marketing stack. Training for your internal team on how to maintain, update, and extend the layer.
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-small text-gray-400">
            <li>→ Brand + voice spec (machine-readable, not a PDF)</li>
            <li>→ ICP + buyer context (personas, pain hierarchy, objection framing)</li>
            <li>→ Competitive framing (displacement narratives, differentiation)</li>
            <li>→ Content architecture (topic clusters, atomization frameworks, templates)</li>
            <li>→ Machine readability + distribution schema (JSON-LD, llms.txt, entity definitions)</li>
            <li>→ Measurement targets (revenue influence, feedback loops)</li>
            <li>→ Team training and handoff</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Advisor Retainer -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-small text-teal-400 mb-2">Ongoing</p>
          <h3 class="text-heading mb-4">Advisor Retainer</h3>
          <p class="text-body text-gray-400 mb-6">
            Monthly signal review plus layer update cycle plus agent deployment guidance. The layer doesn't go stale because the retainer is the update cycle. Covers both Stage 3 (humans + AI assist) and Stage 4 (humans + agents running routines).
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-small text-gray-400">
            <li>→ Monthly signal review (what ranked, converted, missed, shifted)</li>
            <li>→ Layer update and version control</li>
            <li>→ Agent deployment guidance as new use cases emerge</li>
            <li>→ Competitive framing refresh</li>
            <li>→ Measurement framework calibration</li>
            <li>→ Marketing org evolution advisory</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Also Available -->
  <section class="section border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-heading mb-8" data-animate>Also Available</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8" data-animate-stagger="0.12">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-subheading mb-2"><a href="/gravity-audit" class="text-blue-bright hover:text-white transition-colors">Gravity Audit™</a></h3>
          <p class="text-body text-gray-400">
            A standalone AI visibility and GTM diagnostic. Tests 15-20 buyer queries across ChatGPT, Perplexity, and AI Overviews. Audits content authority and organic pull. Delivers findings, priority gap list, and 30-day action plan. Often serves as the entry point to the full Intelligence Layer engagement.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-subheading mb-2"><a href="/gtm-strategy-consultant" class="text-blue-bright hover:text-white transition-colors">GTM Strategy</a></h3>
          <p class="text-body text-gray-400">
            Focused GTM engagements — positioning, ICP development, pipeline mechanics, competitive framing. For companies that need strategic clarity before building infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Process -->
  <section class="section border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-heading mb-12" data-animate>How It Starts</h2>
      <div class="space-y-12" data-animate-stagger="0.12">
        <div class="flex gap-8">
          <span class="text-display text-gray-700 shrink-0">01</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-subheading mb-2">Conversation</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-gray-400">
              30 minutes. You tell me what you're seeing — or not seeing — in your marketing results. I tell you whether the Intelligence Layer diagnostic is the right move or if something else would serve you better. No pitch, just conversation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-8">
          <span class="text-display text-gray-700 shrink-0">02</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-subheading mb-2">Diagnostic</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-gray-400">
              2-4 weeks. I assess your marketing function across all six components of the Intelligence Layer. You get a gap analysis, architecture blueprint, and build plan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-8">
          <span class="text-display text-gray-700 shrink-0">03</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-subheading mb-2">Build</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-gray-400">
              30-90 days. The Intelligence Layer gets built, deployed, and connected to your stack. Your team gets trained. The system compounds from day one.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-display mb-6" data-animate>Before you hire, build, or buy</h2>
      <p class="text-body-lg text-gray-400 mb-8 max-w-prose" data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
        Know what you're actually missing. The diagnostic tells you where you stand across all six layers — and what to do about it.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:nick@strategnik.com" class="text-blue-bright hover:text-white transition-colors" data-animate data-animate-delay="0.2">
        Start the conversation →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
